<b>6th May 2009</b><br />
New executive team was elected and started its work on building the supercomputer.<br />
<br />

<b>3rd June 2008</b><br />
Keep tuned to the site for acctivity. We will hopefully be continuing our work on the Distributed Linux PS3 Cluster, during the summer.<br />
<br />

<b>16th November 2007</b><br />
HCC is having its 2007-2008 year kickoff event tonight.  We're looking for all Electrical and Computer engineers to come out, regardless of their year.  If you're interested in computers, whether you have something to contribute or not - come join us!  FREE PIZZA & DRINKS will be served.<br />
<br />
<b><i>Where: ENGLG21<br />
When:  16th November 2007<br />
Time:  6:00pm</i></b><br />


<br />

<b>16th November 2007</b><br />
For those of you planning on taking part in the upcoming Industrial Internship Program of next summer, you may have noticed employers have a sizable list of programming background requirements such as:<br /><br />

PERL , JAVA, C, SHELL SCRIPTING, SQL <br /><br />

The Hobby Computer Club is proud to present its first Information Tutorial of the 07-08 year on :  PERL<br />
The topic will be presented by 3rd Year Electrical Engineering master, John Chia.<br /><br />

Come out and learn the basics that employers are expecting you to know!   Get a head start on the competition and learn useful information along the way!
<br />
<br />
<b><i>Where: ENG406<br />
When:  20th November 2007<br />
Time:  5:00pm</i></b><br />


